Adding a special feature for selecting the targets.

In[]:
average_consumption = df['annual_consume'].mean()
average_smartmeter_percent = df['smartmeter_perc'].mean()

df['high_energy_low_smartmeters'] = ((df['annual_consume'] > average_consumption) & (df['smartmeter_perc'] < average_smartmeter_percent))
In[]:

Target Areas

In[]:
lat_center, lon_center = 52.1326, 5.2913 #Locking Map in Netherlands

fig = px.choropleth_mapbox(target_areas, 
                           geojson=geo_json_data, 
                           locations='zipcode_processed', 
                           color='smartmeter_perc',
                           color_continuous_scale="Viridis", 
                           mapbox_style="carto-positron",
                           zoom=7,
                           featureidkey='properties.pc4_code', 
                           center = {"lat": lat_center, "lon": lon_center},
                           opacity=0.5,
                           labels={'smartmeter_perc':'Smart Sensors Percentage'}
                          )

fig.update_layout(margin={"r":0,"t":0,"l":0,"b":0})
fig.show()
